"{\"uid\": \"eonline.com-news-1406109-olympic-judge-defends-australian-breakdancer-rayguns-originality\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"After Rachael \\\"Raygun\\\" Gunn's breakdancing performance at the 2024 Olympics caused controversy, judge Martin Gilian came to her defense.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4364388703105216e-16, \"text\": \"Rachael\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\"}, {\"begin\": 102, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999999993697202, \"rank\": 6.30088446019687e-10, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This judge is breaking down some Olympic rules.\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 185, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Australian breakdancerRachael \\\"Raygun\\\" Gunnwent viral for her polarizing performance at the2024 Olympics, chief breakdancing judgeMartin Giliandetailed why her moves should not be under such scrutiny.\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's all about originality and it's all about bringing something new to the table and representing your country or region,\\\" Gilian explained during a press conference, perCNN, noting Gunn's moves.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.9999999953261067, \"rank\": 4.672574003861481e-09, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is exactly what Raygun was doing, she got inspired by her surroundings, which in this case, for example, was a kangaroo.\\\"\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.680754383919646e-54, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And while Gunn's moves went viral on social media, Gilian emphasized that the judges table was fairly unphased.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 732, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.9999999953261067, \"rank\": 4.672574003861481e-09, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She created some original moves which could be maybe funny or entertaining for others, but for us, she basically represented breaking and hip hop,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She was trying to be original and bring something new to the table.\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1062, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From our perspective, that was nothing really shocking.\\\"\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1119, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, other members of the breaking community expressed concern over the less-than-positive responses to Gunn's performance.\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.9999999953261067, \"rank\": 4.672574003861481e-09, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That should not happen in our world,\\\" general secretary of the World DanceSport FederationSergey Nifontovsaid, per CNN.\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2921985799697867e-35, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Something is going in the wrong direction.\\\"\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For her part, Gunn-who failed to earn any points during her Aug. 9 performance- understands that not everyone will see the artistry of her moves.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, she stands by her participation in the Paris games.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23372080076564e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was never going to beat these girls on what they do best-their power moves,\\\" she shared ata press conference Aug. 10.\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What I bring is creativity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, it was most important to Gunn that her routine at theParis Olympicsbe original.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.9999999953261067, \"rank\": 4.672574003861481e-09, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Creativity is really important to me,\\\" the 36-year-old added.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I go out there, and I show my artistry.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes it speaks to the judges, and sometimes it does not.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do my thing, and it represents art.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is what it is about.\\\"\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Keep reading for more controversies from the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jordan Chiles Medal Controversy  After the U.S. gymnast won bronze in the women's gymnastics individual floor exercise final, the Romanian Gymnastics Federation and Romanian finalistsAna Maria BarbosuandSabrina Maneca-Voinea, who came in fourth and fifth place, filed an appeal with the Court of Arbitration for Sport.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2157, \"end\": 2170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 2287, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Romanian Gymnastics Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_Gymnastics_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 2322, \"end\": 2330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.5581242078450596, \"rank\": 0.7917152535434485, \"text\": \"Romanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 2344, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"score\": 0.9662046651955715, \"rank\": 0.03497740801266825, \"text\": \"Maria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Romanian side argued that an inquiry that Chiles' coach had submitted at the competition that had led to the athlete's score to be raised by 0.1 of a point should not have been granted because it was submitted four seconds past a one-minute deadline.\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2481, \"end\": 2489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.5581242078450596, \"rank\": 0.7917152535434485, \"text\": \"Romanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The court agreed and ruled that the U.S. athlete's initial score of 13.666 would be reinstated, a decision also adopted later by the International Gymnastics Federation, which said in a statement that it had modified the rankings to put Barbosu in third place.\", \"from\": 2733, \"to\": 2993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympics Committee then announced that it \\\"will reallocate the bronze medal to Ana Barbosu (Romania),\\\" adding, \\\"We are in touch with the NOC of Romania to discuss the reallocation ceremony and with USOPC regarding the return of the bronze medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 2995, \"to\": 3259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympics Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.999999965591997, \"rank\": 3.1876760213469843e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.999999965591997, \"rank\": 3.1876760213469843e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The\\u00a0 U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Committee says it plans to appeal the decision.\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada Boots Women's Soccer Coach  The 2024 Olympics had barely begun whenBev Priestman, head coach of the\\u00a0 Canadian women's soccer team, wasremoved from her post by Canada Soccerafter her staff was accused of using drones to spy on the New Zealand team ahead of their group stage match.\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3451, \"end\": 3459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.999370939779389, \"rank\": 0.0006294561863609448, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3509, \"end\": 3515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9594510851851211, \"rank\": 0.04226261546270037, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 3580, \"end\": 3591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9944650704559544, \"rank\": 0.005565725789893081, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Additional information has come to our attention regarding previous\\u00a0drone use against opponents, predating the Paris 2024 Olympic Games,\\\" Canada Soccer CEO and general secretaryKevin Bluesaid in a July 25 statement explaining the decision.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In light of these new revelations, Canada Soccer has made the decision to suspend\\u2026Bev Priestman for the remainder of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games, and until the completion of our recently announced independent external review.\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 4098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3907, \"end\": 3920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3954, \"end\": 3967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bev Priestman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Priestman apologized, saying in a statement, \\\"I am absolutely heartbroken for the players, and I would like to apologize from the bottom of my heart for the impact this situation has had on all of them.\", \"from\": 4098, \"to\": 4301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The team, which won gold in Tokyo, is \\\"a group of people who care very much about sportsmanship and integrity,\\\" she continued.\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4330, \"end\": 4335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999313449758, \"rank\": 6.865477191263158e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As the leader of the team on the field, I want to take accountability, and I plan to fully co-operate with the [Canadian Soccer Association] investigation.\\\"\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4542, \"end\": 4569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Soccer Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Korea Mistaken for North Korea During the Opening Ceremony  As the boat carrying athletes from South Korea came into view during the July 26 Opening Ceremony, they were incorrectly announced in both French and English as being from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea-which is North Korea.South Korea, meanwhile, is the Republic of Korea.In a July 27 statement, the International Olympic Committee noted, \\\"We deeply apologize for the mistake that occurred when introducing the Korean team during the Opening Ceremony broadcast.\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 5127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4588, \"end\": 4599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.61675864572654e-15, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4613, \"end\": 4624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.007332340139999e-17, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4689, \"end\": 4700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.61675864572654e-15, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4895, \"end\": 4900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.9839061834677026e-15, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4966, \"end\": 4997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5077, \"end\": 5083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.6014393833790486, \"rank\": 0.662677948328006, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"IOC PresidentThomas Bachalso called South Korean PresidentYoon Suk Yeolto apologize, per the chief executive's office, which relayed that Yoon told Bach the people of South Korea were \\\"very shocked and embarrassed\\\" by the mistake.\", \"from\": 5127, \"to\": 5358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5170, \"end\": 5176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.6014393833790486, \"rank\": 0.662677948328006, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 5276, \"end\": 5280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0850534186394115e-22, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 5295, \"end\": 5306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.61675864572654e-15, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An IOC spokesperson called the error an \\\"operational mistake\\\" that was \\\"clearly deeply regrettable.\", \"from\": 5359, \"to\": 5458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5362, \"end\": 5365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.802009734552871e-74, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Parade order is determined alphabetically according to the host nation's language-minus Greece, which always goes first as the home of the first Olympics, and the host nation goes last.\", \"from\": 5458, \"to\": 5644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5547, \"end\": 5553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999999996771294, \"rank\": 3.228312273185715e-10, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Korea was the 48th country in the Parade of Nations, while North Korea was 153rd.\", \"from\": 5645, \"to\": 5732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5645, \"end\": 5656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.61675864572654e-15, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 5710, \"end\": 5721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.007332340139999e-17, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Wrong Kind of Splash  British commentatorBob Ballardwas pulled from Eurostar's Olympics coverage for making a remark that was widely derided as sexist after Australian swimmersMollie O'Callaghan,Shayna Jack,Emma McKeonandMeg Harriswon gold in the 4x100-meter freestyle relay.\", \"from\": 5734, \"to\": 6013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5806, \"end\": 5814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.8137242467579486e-11, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}, {\"begin\": 5895, \"end\": 5905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9967777770972861, \"rank\": 0.0032326383022179346, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 5933, \"end\": 5944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shayna Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shayna_Jack\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Well, the women just finishing off,\\\" Ballard said following the race.\", \"from\": 6013, \"to\": 6083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6051, \"end\": 6058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7682137143810416e-16, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You know what women are like\\u2026hanging around, doing their makeup.\", \"from\": 6084, \"to\": 6149, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"His co-commentatorLizzie Simmondsreplied, \\\"Outrageous, Bob.\", \"from\": 6149, \"to\": 6209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the men are doing that as well.\", \"from\": 6210, \"to\": 6249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Calling his comment \\\"inappropriate,\\\" Eurostar said in a July 29 statement Ballard had been removed with \\\"immediate effect\\\" from further coverage.The veteran sportscaster promptly apologized.\", \"from\": 6249, \"to\": 6440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6287, \"end\": 6295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.8137242467579486e-11, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}, {\"begin\": 6324, \"end\": 6331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7682137143810416e-16, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The comments I made during the Australian freestyle relay victory ceremony on Saturday have caused some offence,\\\"he wrote on X.\", \"from\": 6440, \"to\": 6568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6472, \"end\": 6482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9967777770972861, \"rank\": 0.0032326383022179346, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was never my intention to upset or belittle anyone and, if I did, I apologise.\", \"from\": 6569, \"to\": 6651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a massive advocate of women's sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 6652, \"to\": 6694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Rumor That Went Off the Deep End  After speculation that a too-shallow pool inside La Defense Arena was responsible for slower-than-expected times in swimming, the athletes torpedoed the idea that the water wasn't deep enough to smash records.\", \"from\": 6696, \"to\": 6941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's totally a myth,\\\" Team USA'sRegan Smith, who swam away from Paris with five medals, toldNBCOlympics.comafter she andGretchen Walsh,Lilly KingandTorri Huskeset a new world record in the women's 4x100-meter medley.\", \"from\": 6941, \"to\": 7166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7014, \"end\": 7019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23372080076564e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think at first people were very aware of [the lack of new records]\\u2026 So, I think that caused some chatter, like, 'Oh, is it the pool that's doing this?'\", \"from\": 7167, \"to\": 7321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I think as the meet went on, people got used to it, and then I think they got more comfortable with it, and then we started seeing some really fast swims.\", \"from\": 7322, \"to\": 7480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Added four-time medalist Walsh, \\\"I think much of what the Olympics is, and what it represents, makes any pool that it's at feel kind of slow.\", \"from\": 7480, \"to\": 7622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because you have so much pressure on yourself that it is hard at your 100 percent best.\\\"\", \"from\": 7623, \"to\": 7711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmer Sent Home for \\\"Indiscipline\\\"  Brazilian swimmerAna Carolina Vieirawas sent homeafter, according to the Brazilian Olympic Committee, she committed two \\\"acts of indiscipline\\\": She left the Olympic Village with boyfriend/teammateGabriel Santoswithout permission, the BOC said, after acting \\\"in a disrespectful and aggressive manner\\\" in response to a \\\"technical decision made by the Brazilian Swimming Team committee\\\" regarding the 4x100m freestyle relay.In a video titled \\\"How a communication failure destroyed my Olympic dream,\\\"Vieira lamented what happenedbut said, \\\"everything is going to be solved at the right time.\\\"\", \"from\": 7713, \"to\": 8339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7824, \"end\": 7851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brazilian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7908, \"end\": 7923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.713012748496589e-38, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 7985, \"end\": 7988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.683174569207008e-12, \"text\": \"BOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazilian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 8110, \"end\": 8118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"score\": 0.8528029070931846, \"rank\": 0.1726037275711815, \"text\": \"Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another Swimmer Kicked Out for \\\"Inappropriate Atmosphere\\\"  The Paraguayan Olympic Committeeasked swimmerLuana Alonsoto leave the Games, alleging in a statement that she had created an \\\"inappropriate atmosphere at the Heart of Team Paraguay.\", \"from\": 8341, \"to\": 8581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"\\\"We thank her for proceeding as instructed,\\\" the statement continued, \\\"as it was of her own free will that she did not spend the night in the Athletes' Village.\", \"from\": 8581, \"to\": 8742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Southern Methodist University student had seemingly already returned to Texas when she wrote onInstagram Story(translated from Spanish) Aug. 5, \\\"I just wanted to make it clear that I was never removed or expelled from anywhere, stop spreading false information.\", \"from\": 8742, \"to\": 9008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8819, \"end\": 8824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.529104915728366e-11, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\"}, {\"begin\": 8874, \"end\": 8881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9893042561347899, \"rank\": 0.010804712446054084, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not want to give any statement but I am not going to let lies affect me either.\\\"\", \"from\": 9009, \"to\": 9094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MyKayla Skinner vs. Simone Biles  Simone Bileshadalready let it be knownwhat she thought of Tokyo teammateMyKayla Skinner's criticismof the U.S. gymnastics team selected to go to Paris-and Skinner hadapologizedfor saying in a since-deleted video that \\\"the talent and the depth just is not like what it used to be\\\" and that \\\"obviously a lot of girls do not work as hard.\", \"from\": 9096, \"to\": 9465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9116, \"end\": 9128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 9188, \"end\": 9193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999313449758, \"rank\": 6.865477191263158e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But after the 2024 squadwon team gold, Biles captioned a photo of the athletes, \\\"Lack of talent, lazy, olympic champions\\\"-anapparent jabat Skinner's original comment.On Aug. 6, Skinner reiterated in an Instagram video that she had \\\"poorly\\\" articulated her original point.\", \"from\": 9465, \"to\": 9737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9668, \"end\": 9677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.56413765228592e-63, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, she added, the cyberbullying she and her family had been subject to-fallout from hercyberfeud with Biles-had gotten out of hand.Shepleaded with the seven-time gold medalist\\\"to please put a stop to this.\", \"from\": 9738, \"to\": 9945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please ask your followers to stop.\\\"\", \"from\": 9946, \"to\": 9981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beam In a Little Noise, Please  Neither Biles norSuni Leemedaled in beam this year after both gymnasts fell off the apparatus during their final routines.Afterward, Biles commented on the strangely quiet environment during their penultimate event in Paris.\", \"from\": 9983, \"to\": 10239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10233, \"end\": 10238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23372080076564e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was really weird and awkward,\\\" the athlete, who earned bronze on beam in Tokyo, told theAssociated Press.\", \"from\": 10239, \"to\": 10348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10316, \"end\": 10321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999313449758, \"rank\": 6.865477191263158e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have asked several times if we can have some music, or some background noise.\", \"from\": 10349, \"to\": 10430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not really sure what happened there, but yeah, not our favorite.\", \"from\": 10431, \"to\": 10500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"None of us liked it.\", \"from\": 10501, \"to\": 10521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In response to the GOAT's complaint, an International Gymnastics Federation said the atmosphere was \\\"part of the sport presentation plan at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 10521, \"to\": 10673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10541, \"end\": 10545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GOAT_(platform)\", \"score\": 0.7168567345956931, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"GOAT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GOAT_(platform)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GOAT_(platform)\"}, {\"begin\": 10562, \"end\": 10597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 10662, \"end\": 10672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.037172375522277e-45, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Lee noted that \\\"the pressure was definitely on\\\" and \\\"a lot of people were definitely feeling it.\", \"from\": 10673, \"to\": 10770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10674, \"end\": 10677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.99999696069888, \"rank\": 3.0393104830904757e-06, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She wondered if it was so quiet the nearby photographers could hear her breathing.\", \"from\": 10770, \"to\": 10853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It adds to the stress,\\\" Lee said, \\\"just because it's like you, yes, you are the only one up there.\", \"from\": 10853, \"to\": 10952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10878, \"end\": 10881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.99999696069888, \"rank\": 3.0393104830904757e-06, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I was feeling the pressure.\\\"\", \"from\": 10953, \"to\": 10984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics Scoring Shocker  Jordan Chilesseemingly finished out of the running for a medal when she completed her floor exercise final routine and received a score of 13.666, Romania'sAna Barbosuahead of her in third place with a score of 13.700.But afterTeam USA filed a score inquiryon Chiles' behalf and her performance was further reviewed by the judges, her start value was increased by one-tenth of a point.\", \"from\": 10986, \"to\": 11399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, her score was subsequently bumped up to 13.766.\", \"from\": 11400, \"to\": 11460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meaning,she got the bronzeand Barbosu-who was already waving her country's flag in celebration-left the arena in tears.Afterward,Barbosu posted a video of herself competingand wrote, \\\"Thank you to everyone who encouraged me before, during, and after the competition.\\\"\", \"from\": 11461, \"to\": 11728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"5,000 Meters Scoring Shocker  Medal adjustments have not been confined to the gymnastics arena.Kenyan runnerFaith Kipyegonwas initially disqualified for seeming to jostleGudaf Tsegayof Ethiopia during the women's 5,000 meters at the Stade de France on Aug. 5, negating her second-place finish.\", \"from\": 11730, \"to\": 12023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11915, \"end\": 11923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999869678505, \"rank\": 1.1708750609384497e-08, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 11963, \"end\": 11978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have never seen anything like that, in an Olympic final that went on for so long,\\\" commentatorKara Goucher, a two-time Olympian, said on the broadcast, noting that the two women also appeared to exchange heated words.\", \"from\": 12023, \"to\": 12243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12145, \"end\": 12153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1382125992919686e-23, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You see a little bit of elbow, you see a little bit of frustration, but that was many strides and scolding.\", \"from\": 12244, \"to\": 12352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It wasn't until the wee hours of Aug. 6 thatKipyegon found out her silver medal had been reinstated.The Olympic Jury of Appeal ruled that, while there had been \\\"significant contact\\\" between her and Tsegay, \\\"the incident did not warrant a disqualification.\", \"from\": 12352, \"to\": 12608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With that, Italy'sNadia Battocletti-the fourth-place finisher bumped into bronze position by the disqualification-was re-relegated to fourth.\", \"from\": 12608, \"to\": 12750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12620, \"end\": 12625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.8711578508387193, \"rank\": 0.14789752210327825, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming Disqualifications That Stood  Two athletes' hopes of a medal were dashed when they unwittingly broke rules mid-swim, meaning they did not even know they were out until they finished their races.Great Britain'sLuke Greenbankfinished first in his 200-meter backstroke heat but wasdisqualified for staying underwater for further than the maximum 15 metersafter first diving in.\", \"from\": 12752, \"to\": 13135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Win or lose I have always been my own harshest critic but sometimes you have just got to take it as it comes,\\\" hewrote on InstagramAug.\", \"from\": 13135, \"to\": 13271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1.\", \"from\": 13272, \"to\": 13274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can take pride in the fact that I know I was in great shape coming into these games after a tough few years, but this will motivate me to come back stronger.\", \"from\": 13275, \"to\": 13435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A technical error also knockedAlex Walshoff the 200-meter individual medley podium after she finished in the bronze position.\", \"from\": 13435, \"to\": 13561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As she approached the wall during the last leg of her backstroke, she made an illegal turn by starting to flip out of position before she tapped the wall and launched into her breaststroke.\", \"from\": 13562, \"to\": 13751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Still proud,\\\" Walshwrote on InstagramAug.\", \"from\": 13751, \"to\": 13793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"6, thanking her supporters a few days after the race.\", \"from\": 13794, \"to\": 13847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Despite the DQ, this Olympics has been an experience that has left me feeling happy and fulfilled, and I will cherish that forever.\", \"from\": 13848, \"to\": 13980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, everything happens for a reason and there is so much more to be excited about for me in this sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 13981, \"to\": 14092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Something in the Water?\", \"from\": 14094, \"to\": 14117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite $1.53 billion having been budgeted to clean up the perennially polluted Seine, reports swirled for months leading up to the Paris Games about whether it would be safe enough to hold the swimming leg of the triathlons and the 10-kilometer marathons in the river.Paris MayorAnne Hidalgowent for a swimJuly 17 and declared France's most famous body of water good to go-but it's been kind of a s--t show since the Olympics began.On Monday, July 29, swims for the triathletes to familiarize themselves with the Seine were canceled, officials citing poor water quality levels caused by run-off from the weekend's heavy rains (which noticeably started during the July 26 Opening Ceremony).The men's triathlon was thenpostponeda day and rescheduled to follow the women's event on July 31 after organizers deemed bacteria levels too high for a safe swim.Both triathlons were held July 31, day-of tests finding that E. coli and intestinal enterococci levels were low enough to qualify the water as \\\"excellent quality,\\\" per the European Union'sBathing Water Directive.But speculation that the water wasn't safe resumed after two athletes who competed in the triathlon dropped out of the mixed-relay competition, citing respective illnesses (neither of which have been definitively linked to swimming in the Seine).The women's and men's 10km are still scheduled for Aug. 8 and 9, but practices were canceled Aug. 6 after tests showed bacteria levels were once again too high.\", \"from\": 14119, \"to\": 15590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14199, \"end\": 14204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.730384531634953e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 14447, \"end\": 14453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6011159426220894, \"rank\": 0.6261074731685494, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 14633, \"end\": 14638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.730384531634953e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 15153, \"end\": 15158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0187587128384367e-24, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 15423, \"end\": 15428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.730384531634953e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Field Hockey Player Arrested  Australian field hockey playerTom Craigpublicly apologized after being arrested for attempting to buy cocainein Paris two days after the team's quarterfinal loss to the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 15592, \"to\": 15814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15633, \"end\": 15643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9967777770972861, \"rank\": 0.0032326383022179346, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 15745, \"end\": 15750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23372080076564e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 15802, \"end\": 15813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.8474085111888392, \"rank\": 0.18006839298406574, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would firstly like to apologize for what has occurred over the last 24 hours,\\\" he said at an Aug. 7 press conference, per theAustralian Associated Press.\", \"from\": 15816, \"to\": 15972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15955, \"end\": 15971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9686518019046215, \"rank\": 0.03236271076368635, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My actions are my own and by no way reflect the values of my family, my teammates, my friends, the sport and the Australian Olympic team.\", \"from\": 15973, \"to\": 16111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16087, \"end\": 16110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4153954109348177e-17, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have embarrassed you all and I am truly sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 16112, \"to\": 16161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ina statement, an Australian Olympic Committee official called Tom \\\"a good person who had made a poor decision\\\" and said the team would support him if he needed help.\", \"from\": 16163, \"to\": 16329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16181, \"end\": 16209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, the official added, the athlete was losing all of his remaining Olympic privileges, effective immediately.\", \"from\": 16330, \"to\": 16441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your source for entertainment news, celebrities, celeb news, and \\u200bcelebrity gossip.\", \"from\": 16443, \"to\": 16526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Check out the hottest fashion, photos, movies and TV shows!\", \"from\": 16527, \"to\": 16586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92025E!\", \"from\": 16588, \"to\": 16595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Entertainment Television, LLC A Versant Media Company.\", \"from\": 16596, \"to\": 16650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16622, \"end\": 16625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.999999386984388, \"rank\": 6.130156135752995e-07, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}, {\"begin\": 16628, \"end\": 16635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versant\", \"score\": 0.9999999977681, \"rank\": 1.8791121913795894e-09, \"text\": \"Versan